ank]% if option exercised)"\n- **Voting power Class B:** "[blank]% (or [blank]% if option exercised)"\n\nThe fee table references **66,666,670 shares** (and repeatedly lists 66,666,665), but these figures appear in the registration/fee calculation context rather than as confirmed offering sizes.\n\n---\n\n## Underwriting Arrangements\n\n### Syndicate Structure\nA large syndicate of **23 underwriters** is listed, led by:\n\n**Lead bookrunners:**\n- Goldman Sachs & Co. LLC\n- Morgan Stanley\n- BofA Securities\n- Citigroup\n- J.P. Morgan\n\n**Additional managers:**\n- Barclays, Deutsche Bank Securities, RBC Capital Markets, UBS Investment Bank, Wells Fargo Securities, Allen & Company LLC, Cantor, Needham & Company, Raymond James, Societe Generale, Stifel, William Blair, BTG Pactual, ING, Macquarie Capital, Mirae Asset Securities, Mizuho, Santander\n\n### Over-Allotment Option\n> "We have granted to the underwriters an option, exercisable for 30 days after the date of this prospectus, to purchase up to [blank] additional shares of Class A common stock at the public offering price listed on the cover page of this prospectus, less underwriting discounts and commissions."\n\nThe number of over-allotment shares is **omitted**.\n\n### Directed Share Program\n> "At our request, the underwriters have reserved up to [blank] percent of the shares of Class A common stock to be issued by the Company and offered by this prospectus for sale, at the initial public offering price, to [blank]."\n\nBoth the percentage and the intended recipients are **blank**.\n\n### Selling Terms\n- Underwriters may offer shares to dealers at a concession "not in excess of $[blank] per share"\n- The offering price and selling terms "may from time to time be varied by the representatives"\n- Foreign underwriters **ING Bank N.V., Banco BTG Pactual S.A. – Cayman Branch, and Mirae Asset Securities Co., Ltd.** are noted as not being broker-dealers registered with the SEC and therefore may not make sales in the United States\n\n### Settlement\n> "The shares of Class A common stock will be ready for delivery on or about [blank], 2026."\n\nThe specific settlement date is **omitted** (though 2026 is indicated).\n\n---\n\n## Capital Structure Context\n\nThe authorized share structure (at $0.0001 par value) includes:\n- **36,132 million** Class A shares\n- **6,125 million** Class B shares\n- **10,000 million** Class C shares\n- **2,400 million** Class D shares\n- **2,607 million** Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock (2,400 million undesignated)\n\nA **5-for-1 stock split** was approved by the Board in May 2026, applying to all outstanding Class A, B, and C shares.\n\nThe Qualified IPO threshold for preferred stock conversion requires a pre-offering market capitalization of **at least $6.0 billion** and aggregate cash proceeds of **not less than $250 million**.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Omitted/To-Be-Determined Items\n\n| Item | Status |\n|---|---|\n| Initial public offering price (per share and total) | Blank |\n| Price range / midpoint | Referenced but not filled in |\n| Number of Class A shares offered | Blank |\n| Number of over-allotment shares | Blank |\n| Underwriting discounts and commissions | Blank |\n| Proceeds to SpaceX | Blank |\n| Directed share program percentage | Blank |\n| Directed share program recipients | Blank |\n| Dealer concession amount | Blank |\n| Settlement date | Blank (2026 indicated) |\n| Voting power percentages (Class A and B) | Blank |\n| Ownership percentages post-offering | Blank |\n| Price sensitivity amounts | Blank |\n\nThe filing was signed by **Elon Musk** (CEO and CTO) on **May 20, 2026**, in Starbase, Texas, with **Gwynne Shotwell** and **Bret Johnsen** appointed as attorneys-in-fact.',
