        output='# Underwriters, Underwriting Discounts, Commissions, and Syndicate Structure in the SpaceX S-1\n\n## Syndicate Composition and Representatives\n\nThe S-1 identifies a large syndicate of managing underwriters, with **five firms acting as representatives**:\n\n- **Goldman Sachs & Co. LLC**\n- **Morgan Stanley & Co. LLC**\n- **BofA Securities, Inc.**\n- **Citigroup Global Markets Inc.**\n- **J.P. Morgan Securities LLC**\n\nThe full syndicate listed on the cover page includes 23 underwriters across three tiers:\n\n| Tier 1 (Lead) | Tier 2 | Tier 3 |\n|---|---|---|\n| Goldman Sachs & Co. LLC | Barclays | Allen & Company LLC |\n| Morgan Stanley | Deutsche Bank Securities | Cantor |\n| BofA Securities | RBC Capital Markets | Needham & Company |\n| Citigroup | UBS Investment Bank | Raymond James |\n| J.P. Morgan | Wells Fargo Securities | Societe Generale |\n| | | Stifel |\n| | | William Blair |\n| | | BTG Pactual |\n| | | ING |\n| | | Macquarie Capital |\n| | | Mirae Asset Securities |\n| | | Mizuho |\n| | | Santander |\n\nThe underwriting agreement is dated the date of the prospectus, and each underwriter has **severally agreed** to purchase its allocated number of shares. The underwriters\' obligations are subject to receipt and acceptance of shares and their right to reject any order in whole or in part.\n\n---\n\n## Underwriting Discounts and Commissions\n\nThe S-1\'s preliminary pricing table on the cover page presents three line items on a **per-share** and **total** basis (with dollar amounts left blank in this preliminary version):\n\n1. **Initial public offering price**\n2. **Underwriting discounts and commissions** — accompanied by a footnote directing readers to the "Underwriting" section for a description of all underwriting compensation payable in connection with the offering\n3. **Proceeds, before expenses, to Space Exploration Technologies Corp.**\n\nAdditionally, the S-1 discloses that SpaceX will pay all registration expenses under the Investors\' Rights Agreement, **other than underwriting discounts and commissions**, which existing investors would bear.\n\n---\n\n## Over-Allotment (Greenshoe) Option\n\nSpaceX has granted the underwriters an option, **exercisable for 30 days** after the date of the prospectus, to purchase up to an additional [blank] shares of Class A common stock at the public offering price listed on the cover page, **less underwriting discounts and commissions**. If exercised:\n\n- Each underwriter becomes obligated, subject to certain conditions, to purchase approximately the **same percentage** of additional shares as its original allocation bears to the total shares listed for all underwriters in the underwriting table.\n\n---\n\n## Offering Mechanics and Dealer Concessions\n\nThe underwriters initially propose to:\n\n- Offer part of the shares **directly to the public** at the offering price on the cover page\n- Offer part to **certain dealers** at a price representing a concession **not exceeding $[blank] per share** below the public offering price\n\nAfter the initial offering, the **representatives may vary** the offering price and other selling terms from time to time.\n\n---\n\n## Directed Share Program\n\nAt SpaceX\'s request, the underwriters have reserved up to [blank] percent of the Class A common stock for sale, at the IPO price, to [blank] — with a cross-reference to the "Underwriting—Directed Share Program" section.\n\n---\n\n## Foreign Underwriter Restrictions\n\nThree underwriters are **not broker-dealers registered with the SEC** and therefore may not make sales of shares in the United States:\n\n- **ING Bank N.V.**\n- **Banco BTG Pactual S.A. – Cayman Branch**\n- **Mirae Asset Securities Co., Ltd.**\n\n---\n\n## Existing Financial Relationships and Conflicts of Interest\n\nThe S-1 discloses extensive pre-existing relationships between the underwriters and SpaceX, creating potential conflicts of interest:\n\n### SpaceX Bridge Loan ($20 billion)\n- **Lenders or administrative agents**: Affiliates of Goldman Sachs, Morgan Stanley, BofA, Citigroup, and J.P. Morgan\n- **Lenders**: Affiliates of Barclays, Deutsche Bank, RBC Capital Markets, UBS, and Wells Fargo\n\n### SpaceX Credit Facility ($1.5 billion revolving facility)\n| Role | Firms |\n|---|---|\n| **Administrative Agent** | BofA Securities |\n| **Co-Syndication Agents** | Citigroup, Goldman Sachs, Morgan Stanley |\n| **Co-Documentation Agents** | Barclays, Deutsche Bank, Wells Fargo |\n| **Joint Lead Arrangers** | BofA, Citigroup, Goldman Sachs, Morgan Stanley |\n| **Joint Bookrunners** | BofA, Citigroup, Goldman Sachs, Morgan Stanley, Barclays, Deutsche Bank, Wells Fargo |\n| **Lenders** | Barclays, Deutsche Bank, RBC Capital Markets, UBS, Wells Fargo |\n\n### xAI Acquisition Advisory\n- **Morgan Stanley & Co. LLC** advised SpaceX in connection with the acquisition of xAI.\n\n### General Business Activities\nThe underwriters and their affiliates are described as **full-service financial institutions** engaged in securities trading, commercial and investment banking, financial advisory, investment management, investment research, principal investment, hedging, financing, and brokerage activities. They may:\n\n- Make or hold investments and actively trade debt and equity securities (or related derivative securities) and financial instruments for their own accounts and customer accounts\n- Hold long and short positions at any time\n- Provide loans or other financing secured by such securities and instruments\n- Make investment recommendations or publish independent research views\n- Have been, are currently, and may in the future be SpaceX\'s customers in arm\'s-length transactions\n\n---\n\n## Settlement\n\nThe shares of Class A common stock will be **ready for delivery on or about [blank], 2026**.\n\n---\n\n## Key Structural Observations\n\n1. **Massive syndicate**: At 23 underwriters, this is one of the larger IPO syndicates, reflecting the expected size of the offering and the desire for broad distribution capabilities globally.\n\n2. **Five representatives** rather than the typical two or three, signaling an exceptionally large offering where multiple bulge-bracket firms share lead responsibility.\n\n3. **Deep lending relationships**: Nearly every underwriter has an existing lending relationship with SpaceX through either the $20B Bridge Loan or the $1.5B Credit Facility, creating significant **conflicts of interest** that the S-1 flags through standard boilerplate disclosures.\n\n4. **Blank pricing fields**: Consistent with a preliminary S-1, all dollar amounts for offering price, discounts, commissions, share counts, and percentages are left blank, to be filled in through amendments or at pricing.\n\n5. **Exhibit 1.1** (Form of Underwriting Agreement) is filed as an exhibit, with the actual agreement to be executed at pricing.',
