    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output='# SpaceX S-1: Capitalization Table, Pro Forma Capitalization, and Valuation Metrics\n\n## 1. Capitalization Table (As of March 31, 2026)\n\nThe S-1 presents capitalization under three columns: **Actual**, **Pro Forma**, and **Pro Forma as Adjusted**. All dollar figures are in millions.\n\n### Cash\n| Item | Actual | Pro Forma | Pro Forma as Adjusted |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Cash and cash equivalents | $15,852 | $15,852 | $[blank] |\n\n### Long-Term Debt\n| Item | Actual | Pro Forma |\n|---|---|---|\n| SpaceX Credit Facility | $— | $— |\n| SpaceX Bridge Loan | $20,000 | $20,000 |\n| X 2027 and X 2030 Notes | $27 | $27 |\n| Other Financings | $9,105 | $9,105 |\n| Unamortized deferred financing costs | $(21) | $(21) |\n| **Total long-term debt** | **$29,111** | **$29,111** |\n\n### Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock\n- Par value: $0.001\n- Actual: 189,155,861 shares issued; 134,451,267 shares outstanding; carrying value **$7,049 million**\n- Pro Forma and Pro Forma as Adjusted: No shares authorized, issued, or outstanding; value **$0** (reflecting the Preferred Conversion into Class A and Class B common stock)\n\n### Common Stock\n| Class | Par Value | Actual Shares (Issued/Outstanding) | Pro Forma Shares (Issued/Outstanding) | Actual $ | Pro Forma $ |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Class A | $0.001 | 2,964,501,353 issued / 2,882,444,444 outstanding | 36,132,150,000 authorized; 6,824,581,339 issued and outstanding | $3 | $6 |\n| Class B | $0.001 | 2,421,276,530 issued and outstanding | 6,125,000,000 authorized; 5,695,729,430 issued and outstanding | $3 | $6 |\n| Class C | $0.001 | 494,026,445 issued and outstanding | 10,000,000,000 authorized; none issued or outstanding | $0 | $— |\n| Class D | $0.0001 | None | None | $— | $— |\n\n### Preferred Stock (Non-Convertible)\n- Par value: $0.001\n- Actual: No shares issued or outstanding\n- Pro Forma and Pro Forma as Adjusted: 2,400,000,000 shares authorized; none issued or outstanding\n\n### Equity Accounts\n| Item | Actual | Pro Forma |\n|---|---|---|\n| Additional paid-in capital | $74,083 | $81,126 |\n| Accumulated deficit | $(41,311) | $(41,311) |\n| Accumulated other comprehensive income | $1,755 | $1,755 |\n| **Total shareholders\' equity** | **$34,533** | **$41,582** |\n| **Total capitalization** | **$70,693** | **$70,693** |\n\nThe Pro Forma as Adjusted column is left largely blank, pending finalization of the offering price and share count.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Pro Forma Adjustments — Structural Assumptions\n\nThe **Pro Forma** column gives effect to:\n1. **Preferred Conversion** — all outstanding preferred stock converts into Class A and Class B common stock, as if conversion occurred on March 31, 2026.\n2. **Class C Reclassification** — all outstanding Class C common stock reclassifies into Class A common stock, as if reclassification occurred on March 31, 2026.\n3. **Charter effectiveness** — the new charter becomes effective upon completion of the offering.\n\nThe **Pro Forma as Adjusted** column additionally gives effect to:\n1. All pro forma adjustments above.\n2. Sale of Class A common stock in the offering at an assumed initial offering price of **$[blank] per share, which is the midpoint of the price range set forth on the cover page** of the prospectus.\n3. Application of net proceeds as described under "Use of Proceeds."\n\n---\n\n## 3. Price Range Midpoint References\n\nThe S-1 repeatedly references the midpoint of the price range but leaves the actual dollar value blank (standard for a preliminary prospectus):\n\n> "an initial public offering price of $[blank] per share of Class A common stock (the midpoint of the price range set forth on the cover of this prospectus)"\n\n> "the sale of shares of our Class A common stock in this offering at an assumed initial offering price of $[blank] per share, which is the midpoint of the range set forth on the cover page of this prospectus"\n\nThe cover page price table itself is also blank:\n\n| | Per Share | Total |\n|---|---|---|\n| Initial public offering price | $[blank] | $[blank] |\n| Underwriting discounts and commissions | $[blank] | $[blank] |\n| Proceeds, before expenses, to Space Exploration Technologies Corp. | $[blank] | $[blank] |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Fee Table — Proposed Maximum Offering Prices\n\nThe fee table discloses five pricing scenarios for **66,666,670 shares**, escalating in $500 billion increments:\n\n| Shares | Proposed Maximum Aggregate Offering Price |\n|---|---|\n| 66,666,670 | $5,500,000,000,000 ($5.5 trillion) |\n| 66,666,670 | $6,000,000,000,000 ($6.0 trillion) |\n| 66,666,670 | $6,500,000,000,000 ($6.5 trillion) |\n| 66,666,670 | $7,000,000,000,000 ($7.0 trillion) |\n| 66,666,670 | $7,500,000,000,000 ($7.5 trillion) |\n\nThis implies a per-share price range of approximately **$82,500 to $112,500**, with a **midpoint of approximately $97,500 per share** ($6.5 trillion ÷ 66,666,670 shares). The midpoint aggregate offering value would be **$6.5 trillion**.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Valuation Metrics\n\n### Musk Performance Stock Award Valuation Milestones\nIn connection with the xAI Merger, SpaceX assumed a performance stock award originally granted to Elon Musk by xAI on November 26, 2025. The award reflects the right to receive shares of Class A common stock equal to **0.20% of fully diluted capitalization** upon achievement of each of **12 valuation milestones**:\n\n- Range: **$1.065 trillion to $6.565 trillion**\n- Each milestone reflects **$500 billion in additional valuation**\n- The first milestone was achieved prior to the xAI Merger, resulting in issuance of **25,172,695 shares** of Class A common stock to Mr. Musk\n- On March 23, 2026, this award and the 25,172,695 shares were [subject to further adjustment described in the filing]\n\n### Implied Market Capitalization\nBased on the fee table, the proposed maximum aggregate offering prices of **$5.5 trillion to $7.5 trillion** for 66,666,670 shares represent the offering proceeds only. The total market capitalization would be substantially higher when multiplied across all outstanding shares (pro forma approximately 12.5 billion+ shares across Classes A and B combined), potentially implying a total enterprise valuation in the range of **tens of trillions of dollars**.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock Detail\n\n### SpaceX Preferred Stock\n| Series | Dividend/Share | Initial Price/Share | Authorized (M) | Outstanding (M) | Liquidation Pref (M) | Net Carrying Value ($M) |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Series K | $10.20 | $204.00 | 2.7 | 2.5 | 2.5 | $515–518 |\n| Series L | $10.70 | $214.00 | 1.5 | 1.4 | 1.4 | $295 |\n| Series M | $11.00 | $220.00 | 2.7 | 2.6–2.7 | 2.7 | $575–596 |\n| Series N | $13.50 | $270.00 | 9.5 | 9.2–9.3 | 9.3–9.4 | $2,492–2,520 |\n| **Total SpaceX** | | | **206.6–206.8** | **134.6–134.8** | **134.7–135.4** | **$6,475–6,527** (or $7,049–7,099) |\n\n### xAI Preferred Stock\n| Series | Dividend/Share | Initial Price/Share | Authorized (M) | Outstanding (M) | Net Carrying Value ($M) |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Series A | $0.05 | $1.00 | 1,000.0 | 750.0 | $750–753 |\n| Series A-1 | $0.05 | $1.00 | 1,000.0 | — | $— |\n| Series B | $0.60 | $11.97 | 584.9 | 584.9 | $7,001 |\n| Series C | $1.08 | $21.65 | 277.1 | 277.1 | $6,000 |\n| Series D | $1.83 | $36.56 | 174.8 | 120.1 | $4,388–4,390 |\n| Series E | $3.77 | $75.46 | 265.0 | 179.2 | $13,510–13,523 |\n| **Total xAI** | | | **3,301.8** | **1,911.3** | **$31,652–31,664** |\n\n### Combined\n| | Authorized (M) | Outstanding (M) | Net Carrying Value ($M) |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **Total Combined** | **3,508.6** | **2,046.1** | **$38,191–38,751** |\n\n---\n\n## 7. Pro Forma Earnings Per Share\n\n| Item | Three Months Ended March 31, 2026 | Year Ended December 31, 2025 |\n|---|---|---|\n| Net loss attributable to common shareholders | $(4,947)M | $(4,937)M |\n| Pro forma adjustment: reverse deemed dividend on preferred | $565M | $— |\n| **Pro Forma net loss** | **$(4,382)M** | **$(4,937)M** |\n| Weighted average shares (basic, actual) | 3,884M | 2,926M |\n| Pro forma adjustment: Preferred Conversion shares | 6,723M | 6,723M |\n| **Pro forma weighted average shares** | **10,607M** | **9,649M** |\n| **Pro forma net loss per share (basic and diluted)** | **$(0.41)** | **$(0.51)** |\n\n---\n\n## 8. Dilution (Net Tangible Book Value)\n\nThe S-1 states that purchasers of Class A common stock will experience **immediate and substantial dilution** in net tangible book value per share. However, all specific figures are left blank in the preliminary filing:\n\n- Net tangible book value as of March 31, 2026: **$[blank]**, or **$[blank]** per share\n- Adjusted pro forma net tangible book value: **$[blank]**, or **$[blank]** per share\n- Immediate decrease in net tangible book value: **$[blank]** per share\n\n---\n\n## 9. Authorized Capital Structure (Post-Charter)\n\n| Class | Par Value | Authorized Shares |\n|---|---|---|\n| Class A common stock | $0.001 | 36,132 million |\n| Class B common stock | $0.001 | 6,125 million |\n| Class C common stock | $0.001 | 10,000 million |\n| Class D common stock | $0.0001 | 2,400 million |\n| Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock | $0.001 | 2,607 million (2,400 million undesignated) |\n\n### 2026 Stock Split\nIn May 2026, the Board approved a **5-for-1 stock split** for Class A, Class B, and Class C common stock.\n\n---\n\n## 10. Debt Footnotes\n\n1. **SpaceX Credit Facility**: As of April 30, 2026, no borrowings outstanding. In May 2026, amended to increase borrowing capacity to **$5,000 million**. Terminates May 19, 2031.\n2. **SpaceX Bridge Loan**: As of April 30, 2026, **$20,000 million** outstanding. Matures September 2, 2027 (subject to extension).\n3. **Other Financings**: Includes obligations related to certain **AI infrastructure assets** recorded as failed sale-leaseback transactions.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThe SpaceX S-1 capitalization table shows a company with **$70.7 billion in total capitalization** on an actual basis (as of March 31, 2026), with **$29.1 billion in long-term debt** (dominated by the $20 billion Bridge Loan) and **$34.5 billion in shareholders\' equity**. On a pro forma basis (reflecting preferred conversion and Class C reclassification), total capitalization remains $70.7 billion, but shareholders\' equity increases to $41.6 billion as the $7.0 billion preferred stock converts into equity. The Pro Forma as Adjusted figures are largely blank, pending finalization of the offering price at the midpoint of the stated range. The fee table implies an aggregate offering value between **$5.5 trillion and $7.5 trillion** for 66.7 million shares, with a midpoint of **$6.5 trillion** (approximately $97,500 per share). Musk\'s performance award references valuation milestones from **$1.065 trillion to $6.565 trillion**, providing additional context for the company\'s expected valuation trajectory.',
