        name='submit_final_result',
        args='{"final_result":"## Principal Valuation, Underwriting, and Allocation Decisions That Cannot Be Finalized\\n\\nThe SpaceX S-1 (filed May 20, 2026) is explicitly preliminary: *\\"The information in this preliminary prospectus is not complete and may be changed.\\"* The cover-page pricing table, share-count table, and numerous quantitative disclosures throughout the filing contain blank placeholders. Because the final offering size and price range are omitted, institutional investors cannot finalize the following categories of decisions.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 1. VALUATION DECISIONS THAT CANNOT BE FINALIZED\\n\\n**a. IPO Price and Implied Market Capitalization**\\n- The initial public offering price (per share and total) is **blank** on the cover page.\\n- The price range and its midpoint are referenced but **not filled in** (e.g., *\\"an initial public offering price of $[blank] per share … the midpoint of the price range set forth on the cover\\"*).\\n- Without a price, investors cannot compute the implied post-IPO equity market capitalization, enterprise value, or any per-share valuation multiple (P/S, P/B, EV/EBITDA, etc.) against the recast consolidated financials (which include xAI and X Holdings).\\n\\n**b. Dilution to New Investors**\\n- Every figure in the dilution table is **blank**: pre-IPO net tangible book value per share, pro forma adjusted net tangible book value per share, the decrease attributable to new investors, and the dilution per share.\\n- The price-sensitivity analysis (impact of a $1.00 change in IPO price on dilution) is also **entirely blank**.\\n- The comparison table showing average price per share paid by Mr. Musk/existing investors versus new investors cannot be constructed.\\n\\n**c. Pro Forma \\"As Adjusted\\" Capitalization**\\n- The \\"Pro Forma as Adjusted\\" column in the capitalization table (which gives effect to the offering) is **largely blank**, pending the final price and share count. Only the \\"Actual\\" and \\"Pro Forma\\" (pre-offering structural adjustments) columns are populated.\\n\\n**d. Qualified IPO Threshold Confirmation**\\n- The Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock (carrying value ~$7.0 billion for SpaceX preferred; ~$38 billion combined with xAI preferred) automatically converts into Class A and Class B common stock upon a \\"Qualified IPO,\\" defined as:\\n  - Pre-offering market capitalization **≥ $6.0 billion**, AND\\n  - Aggregate cash proceeds to the company **≥ $250 million**.\\n- Because the offering price and size are blank, investors **cannot confirm whether these thresholds will be met**, and therefore cannot independently verify that the Preferred Conversion—a foundational pro forma assumption throughout the filing—will actually occur.\\n\\n**e. Musk Performance Stock Award Milestones**\\n- The xAI-originated performance award grants Mr. Musk 0.20% of fully diluted capitalization upon each of 12 valuation milestones ranging from **$1.065 trillion to $6.565 trillion** (in $500 billion increments). The first milestone was achieved pre-merger. Whether subsequent milestones are triggered depends on the post-IPO valuation, which cannot be assessed without a price range.\\n\\n**f. SEC Fee Table as a Floor Estimate**\\n- The SEC registration fee is stated as **$138,100**. At the FY2026 Section 6(b) rate of $138.10 per $1 million, this implies a proposed maximum aggregate offering price of approximately **$1.0 billion** for fee-calculation purposes only. This is a regulatory placeholder, not a confirmed offering size, and provides no usable price-per-share or final proceeds figure.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 2. UNDERWRITING DECISIONS THAT CANNOT BE FINALIZED\\n\\n**a. Underwriting Discounts and Commissions**\\n- Both the per-share and total underwriting discounts and commissions are **blank** on the cover page. Investors cannot assess the gross spread, the effective cost of capital, or the total compensation payable to the 23-firm syndicate (led by Goldman Sachs, Morgan Stanley, BofA, Citigroup, and J.P. Morgan as representatives).\\n\\n**b. Net Proceeds to SpaceX**\\n- \\"Proceeds, before expenses, to SpaceX\\" is **blank** on the cover page.\\n- The Use of Proceeds section references net proceeds of **$[blank]** (or **$[blank]** if the over-allotment is exercised in full) at an assumed midpoint price of **$[blank]** per share. Investors cannot quantify the capital available for the stated uses (AI compute infrastructure, launch infrastructure, satellite constellations, and general corporate purposes).\\n\\n**c. Over-Allotment (Greenshoe) Option Size**\\n- The number of additional shares purchasable under the 30-day over-allotment option is **blank**. Investors cannot assess the potential dilutive impact or the stabilizing effect of the greenshoe on post-IPO trading.\\n\\n**d. Dealer Concession**\\n- The maximum per-share concession to selling dealers is **blank** (*\\"not in excess of $[blank] per share\\"*).\\n\\n**e. Settlement Date**\\n- The delivery/settlement date is **blank** (*\\"on or about [blank], 2026\\"*), though 2026 is indicated.\\n\\n**f. Final Underwriting Agreement**\\n- Exhibit 1.1 is filed as a **form** of underwriting agreement; the definitive agreement will be executed at pricing. Final terms (including any lock-up modifications, expense allocations, and indemnification specifics) are not yet fixed.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 3. ALLOCATION DECISIONS THAT CANNOT BE FINALIZED\\n\\n**a. Total Shares Offered and Post-Offering Share Count**\\n- The number of Class A shares offered by the company is **blank** (including the alternative count if the over-allotment is exercised).\\n- Class A shares outstanding after the offering: **blank**.\\n- Class B shares outstanding after the offering: **blank**.\\n- Without these figures, investors cannot compute the post-IPO public float, free-float percentage, or total shares outstanding.\\n\\n**b. Post-Offering Voting Power and Ownership Percentages**\\n- Voting power percentages for Class A and Class B (with and without over-allotment exercise) are **blank**.\\n- Mr. Musk\'s post-offering beneficial ownership percentages (Class A shares, Class B shares, and total voting power) are **blank**.\\n- Investors cannot quantify the extent of the dual-class control structure (Class B = 10 votes/share; Class B elects 51% of the board) or confirm controlled-company status thresholds.\\n\\n**c. Directed Share Program (DSP) Parameters**\\n- The percentage of shares reserved for the DSP is **blank**.\\n- The intended recipients are **blank** (the DSP is administered by Morgan Stanley for employees and designated individuals; DSP shares are exempt from lock-up).\\n- Investors cannot determine how many shares are effectively removed from the public offering pool.\\n\\n**d. Lock-Up Share Counts and Release Schedule**\\n- The aggregate shares subject to the 366-day lock-up (Musk and significant investors; 100% of Musk\'s shares; no early release for Musk) is **blank**.\\n- The shares subject to the 180-day lock-up (company, directors, officers, remaining shareholders) are **blank**.\\n- The staggered early-release quantities (up to 20% after Q2 2026 earnings; up to 10% additional if price ≥ 130% of IPO for 5 of 10 days; up to 7% at 70/90/105/120/135 days; up to 28% after Q3 2026 earnings; remainder at 180 days) are all expressed as percentages of **blank** share counts.\\n- Investors cannot model the lock-up expiry supply overhang.\\n\\n**e. Registration Rights Share Counts**\\n- The approximate number of shares subject to demand and piggyback registration rights under the Investors\' Rights Agreement is **blank**, preventing assessment of future follow-on supply.\\n\\n**f. Retail Allocation Architecture (Disclosed but Unquantified)**\\n- The framework for retail distribution is disclosed: five online brokerage platforms (Charles Schwab, Fidelity, Robinhood, SoFi, E*TRADE by Morgan Stanley) as selling group members, plus a 5% cap on discretionary-account sales. However, the actual share counts allocated to each channel depend on the final offering size, which is blank.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Summary Table: Omitted Items by Category\\n\\n| Category | Omitted/Blank Items |\\n|---|---|\\n| **Valuation** | IPO price (per share & total); price range/midpoint; implied market cap; all dilution figures; price-sensitivity amounts; pro forma as-adjusted capitalization; Qualified IPO threshold confirmation; performance-award milestone triggers |\\n| **Underwriting** | Underwriting discounts & commissions; net proceeds; greenshoe size; dealer concession; settlement date; definitive underwriting agreement terms |\\n| **Allocation** | Shares offered; post-offering share counts (Class A & B); voting power %; ownership %; DSP percentage & recipients; lock-up share counts; registration-rights share counts; retail channel allocations |\\n\\n### What IS Disclosed (Structural Framework)\\n\\nWhile the quantitative parameters are blank, the S-1 does establish the structural framework:\\n- **Syndicate**: 23 underwriters, 5 representatives (Goldman Sachs, Morgan Stanley, BofA, Citigroup, J.P. Morgan).\\n- **Lock-up architecture**: 366-day for Musk/significant investors (no early release for Musk); 180-day for all others, with staggered early-release provisions tied to earnings dates and price thresholds.\\n- **DSP**: Administered by Morgan Stanley; shares exempt from lock-up; unsold shares revert to public pool.\\n- **Retail platforms**: Schwab, Fidelity, Robinhood, SoFi, E*TRADE at same price/timing as institutions; 5% discretionary-account cap.\\n- **Listing**: Nasdaq and Nasdaq Texas under \\"SPCX\\"; controlled-company status expected.\\n- **Primary-only offering**: No selling stockholders; all proceeds to the company.\\n- **Capital structure**: Dual-class (A=1 vote, B=10 votes, C=0 votes); 5-for-1 stock split effected May 2026; Preferred Conversion and Class C Reclassification assumed pre-IPO.\\n\\nInstitutional investors can evaluate the structural design of the offering but cannot perform any quantitative valuation, underwriting-cost, or allocation-impact analysis until the final offering size and price range are inserted via amendment or at pricing.\\n\\n---\\n\\n{\\n  \\"sources\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\"url\\": \\"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1181412/000162828026036936/spaceexplorationtechnologi.htm\\",\\n      \\"name\\": \\"SpaceX S-1 Registration Statement (filed May 20, 2026)\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\"url\\": \\"https://www.sec.gov/rules-regulations/fee-rate-advisories/2026-1\\",\\n      \\"name\\": \\"SEC Section 6(b) Filing Fee Rate Advisory for Fiscal Year 2026 ($138.10 per $1 million, effective October 1, 2025)\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}"}',
